title: Google\Cloud\Dataflow\V1beta3\PubsubLocation
name: PubsubLocation
description:
Identifies a pubsub location to use for transferring data into or out of a streaming Dataflow job.

Generated from protobuf message google.dataflow.v1beta3.PubsubLocation

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.topic
params.description: A pubsub topic, in the form of "pubsub.googleapis.com/topics//"

params.name: data.subscription
params.description: A pubsub subscription, in the form of "pubsub.googleapis.com/subscriptions//"

params.name: data.timestamp_label
params.description: If set, contains a pubsub label from which to extract record timestamps. If left empty, record timestamps will be generated upon arrival.

params.name: data.id_label
params.description: If set, contains a pubsub label from which to extract record ids. If left empty, record deduplication will be strictly best effort.

params.name: data.drop_late_data
params.description: Indicates whether the pipeline allows late-arriving data.

params.name: data.tracking_subscription
params.description: If set, specifies the pubsub subscription that will be used for tracking custom time timestamps for watermark estimation.

params.name: data.with_attributes
params.description: If true, then the client has requested to get pubsub attributes.
